Umm.. NO! x2   </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">Righty-o.. We&#39;ve switched things up a little, and it seems to work a bit more consistantly.<br>
<br>
Prek starts it off this time, grabbing a Crystal Parmalag and any of the other three you feel you need immediately. The Crystal should be held for when Radget comes out..<br>
<br>
Radget goes second this time.. Strategy with her is simple, just feed the opponant a steady diet of Parmalags. When they get tired, Radget can &#39;refresh&#39; them to like-new condition. ^.^ When she comes out, you&#39;ll want to put out the Crystal Parmalag and one or two others.. Stay cautious for removal, be it mass or otherwise.. If you&#39;ve got the Cloaks in, Radget oughta be wearing one by now. Trygar should recieve the second.. Also, for Trygar, you should try to save the Digging Goggles and Pylofufs. If you need to play some of them, go ahead as he&#39;ll pick up the Boots and a &#39;fuf from the discard pile.<br>
<br>
Things that can really hurt this deck include Rayje&#39;s Belt.. Therefore the emphisis on Relic removal with the &#39;Stalkers, or the pre-emptive Rayje&#39;s Cloaks.. </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000"> </Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">DeckTech <BR> For the Players, By the Players  <BR>www.decktech.net </FONT></TD></TR></table> 
